   <question id="q1">
      <body>
         <p>Since both genders are equally likely, and since the gender of one child does not affect
               the gender of another,
               <?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101108T094051-0500" content="we&apos;re in a situation where"?><?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101108T094051-0500"?>in
               this scenario<?oxy_insert_end?> all 8 outcomes are equally likely (each having
               probability 1/8).</p>
         <p>Now we're getting to our event of interest: "Having exactly two girls." Let's denote
               this event by A.</p>
         <p>How many of the 8 outcomes satisfy (or make up) event A? List them.</p>
      </body>
      <short_answer id="A"/>
      <part>
         <response input="A" match="*" score="1"/>
         <explanation>
            <p>There are three possible outcomes that make up (or satisfy)
                  <?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101106T124006-0400" content="event "?>event
                  A:</p>
            <p>(BGG), (GBG), (GGB)</p>
         </explanation>
      </part>
   </question></page>
